main event: Two objects, shaped like derby hats, with white domes and three blue lights on the bottom part, were seen three times, changing spatially at the New Castle AFB in Delaware on 6 November 1954.
interesting points: The objects were described as having a white dome and three blue lights on the bottom, resembling derby hats.
The sighting lasted for three to four minutes, with the objects changing spatially.
The conclusion of the investigation indicated that the sighting could have been two private aircraft or possibly astronomical, but it was ultimately labeled as unknown.
The report references erratic behavior by the objects, which adds to the mystery of the sighting.
There were no photographs of the UFO sighting available for documentation.
